OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FUK family to apologise in  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25FGrenada over slavery       
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A UK family will publicly apologise to 
OL,6, the people of the Caribbean island of  
OL,7, Grenada, where its ancestors had more  
OL,8, than 1,000 slaves in the 19th Century. 
OL,10,FThe aristocratic Trevelyan family, who 
OL,11,Fowned six sugar plantations in Grenada,
OL,12,Fwill also pay reparations.             
OL,14,FBBC reporter Laura Trevelyan, a family 
OL,15,Fmember, visited Grenada in 2022.       
OL,17,FShe was shocked that her ancestors had 
OL,18,Fbeen compensated by the UK government  
OL,19,Fwhen slavery was abolished in 1833 -   
OL,20,Fbut freed African slaves got nothing.  
